==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dactylic
<hw>Dac*tyl"ic</hw> <pr>(d⟦acr⟧k*t⟦icr⟧l"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>dactylicus</ets>, Gr. <grk>daktyliko`s</grk>, fr.
<grk>da`ktylos</grk>.]</ety> <def>Pertaining to, consisting chiefly or
wholly of, dactyls; <as>as, <ex>dactylic</ex> verses</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dactylic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Dactylic
<hw>Dac*tyl"ic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A line consisting
chiefly or wholly of dactyls; <as>as, these lines are
<ex>dactylics</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>Dactylic meters.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>dactylioglyph</ent>⟦br⟧
